<p>We consider four critical times: 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1003668.e312.jpg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>, 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1003668.e313.jpg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>, 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1003668.e314.jpg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>, and 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1003668.e315.jpg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>. The first, 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1003668.e316.jpg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>, is the time at which the optimal sampling strategy switches from sampling only infected hosts to sampling only the vector population. The time at which the optimal sampling strategy switches from sampling infected hosts to sampling recovered hosts is 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1003668.e317.jpg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>. The times 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1003668.e318.jpg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula> and 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1003668.e319.jpg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula> give the critical switches from sampling only the vector population to recovered hosts or vice-versa. The other potential critical times 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1003668.e320.jpg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula> and 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1003668.e321.jpg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula> are not considered here because they do not exist at early times for for these initial conditions 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1003668.e322.jpg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>, but expressions are given for alternative initial conditions in 
 <xref ref-type="supplementary-material" rid="pcbi.1003668.s006">Text S4</xref>.
</p>
